# SJMS-5 — Code owners
#
# Every file in this repository has an implicit default owner
# (`RJK134`) through the catch-all at the top of the list. Subsequent
# entries override it for security-critical, governance-critical, or
# high-blast-radius paths so those changes cannot merge without an
# explicit code-owner review when the branch protection rule
# "Require review from Code Owners" is enabled.
#
# Bus-factor (deep-review P0 #6, closed via Phase 0 batch 0K):
# every owner line names BOTH `@RJK134` and `@SECOND_OWNER`. The latter
# is a deliberate placeholder. Operator action required before Phase 1
# closes: search-and-replace `@SECOND_OWNER` for the agreed second
# reviewer's GitHub login. The branch-protection rule "Require 2
# reviewers including code-owners" (mandated from Phase 0 close per
# docs/operations/ci-and-branch-protection.md §2) is honestly met only
# after that replacement.
#
# See: https://docs.github.com/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-security/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

